==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Red-letter
<hw>Red"-let`ter</hw> <pr>(-l?t`t?r)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to a red letter; marked by red letters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Red-letter day</b></col>, <cd>a day that is fortunate or
auspicious; -- so called in allusion to the custom of marking holy days,
or saints' days, in the old calendars with red letters.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Red-light district</ent>⟦br⟧
